{
  "page": "House Haen",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold\">House Haen</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\"><div></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Region</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>House Haen</b> was a noble house from <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#House_Haen_at_the_end_of_the_third_century\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">House Haen at the end of the third century</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Historical_Members\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Historical Members</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Haen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>At the time of the <a href=\"/index.php/Regency_of_Aegon_III\" title=\"Regency of Aegon III\">regency</a> of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon III Targaryen</a>, House Haen was led by <a href=\"/index.php/Magister\" title=\"Magister\">Magister</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Torreo_Haen\" title=\"Torreo Haen\">Torreo Haen</a>. In <a href=\"/index.php/133_AC\" title=\"133 AC\">133&#160;AC</a>, Torreo sent his daughter <a href=\"/index.php/Myrmadora_Haen\" title=\"Myrmadora Haen\">Myrmadora</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> to be presented as a potential wife to King Aegon III in the <a href=\"/index.php/Maiden%27s_Day_Ball\" title=\"Maiden&#39;s Day Ball\">Maiden's Day Ball</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the fall of the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Rogare\" title=\"House Rogare\">Rogare family</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/135_AC\" title=\"135 AC\">135&#160;AC</a>, a bloody struggle ensued in the resulting power vacuum. Torreo was elevated to <a href=\"/index.php/First_Magister\" title=\"First Magister\">First Magister</a>. However, at the feast he held to celebrate his new position, he was <a href=\"/index.php/Poison\" title=\"Poison\">poisoned</a>, along with his wife, daughters (including Myrmadora), siblings, and supporters.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"House_Haen_at_the_end_of_the_third_century\">House Haen at the end of the third century</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Haen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: House Haen at the end of the third century\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The known Haens during the timespan of the events described in <i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Song_of_Ice_and_Fire\" title=\"A Song of Ice and Fire\">A Song of Ice and Fire</a></i> are:\n</p>\n<ul><li>no member has appeared yet.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Historical_Members\">Historical Members</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Haen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Historical Members\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Torreo_Haen\" title=\"Torreo Haen\">Torreo Haen</a>, briefly <a href=\"/index.php/First_Magister\" title=\"First Magister\">First Magister</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a>\n<ul><li>Torreo's wife\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Myrmadora_Haen\" title=\"Myrmadora Haen\">Myrmadora Haen</a>, one of his daughters</li>\n<li>Other daughters</li></ul></li></ul></li>\n<li>Torreo's siblings</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=House_Haen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabunder_the_regents_-_war_and_peace_and_cattle_shows.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Under the Regents - War and Peace and Cattle Shows.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Lysene Spring and the End of Regency.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403155828\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.069 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.259 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 443/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 10015/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 2246/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 492/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1353/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.170/7.000 seconds\nLua virtual size: 5.45 MB/50 MB\nLua estimated memory usage: 0 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  249.756      1 -total\n 90.98%  227.223      1 Template:Noble_House\n 90.62%  226.340      1 Template:Infobox\n  8.94%   22.320     10 Template:Infobox_value\n  4.27%   10.663      2 Template:Date\n  3.60%    8.999      2 Template:Ref\n  2.28%    5.694      2 Template:Ref/core\n  1.44%    3.600      1 Template:Infobox_label\n  0.93%    2.315      1 Template:References\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:26018-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403155828 and revision id 294964\n -->\n",
